<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="269" pageId="4" pageNumber="267" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1238,2093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,518,1922,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rubite, C. Justo, P. Villasenor &amp; C. W. Lin. A, B. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[518,666,1922,1948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="4" pageNumber="267" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tarangban">
<emphasis box="[518,666,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">B. tarangban</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Tarangban Falls, Calbayog City, 
<collectingRegion box="[1197,1269,1922,1948]" country="Philippines" name="Samar" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">Samar</collectingRegion>
Island. It grows on semishaded rocky slopes near the falls at 
<quantity box="[635,706,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="267" unit="m" value="160.0">160 m</quantity>
in elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1238,2093]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1452,158,257]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="268" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1994,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rubite, C. Justo, P. Villasenor &amp; C. W. Lin. A, B. Habit" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,441,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="4" pageNumber="267" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tarangban">
<emphasis box="[294,441,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">B. tarangban</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[583,746,1994,2020]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="4" pageNumber="267" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="biliranensis">
<emphasis box="[583,746,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="267">B. biliranensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having ovate stipules, obliquely ovate, strongly inequilateral cordate leaves where adaxial surface is glabrous and abaxial surface is associated with hairs at the veins; long petioles (
<quantity box="[145,259,2066,2093]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="267" unit="cm" value="14.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="11.0">11–18 cm</quantity>
); long inflorescence dichotomously branching 4 to 5 times. However, the new species differs in having long internodes 
<quantity box="[261,348,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="268" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4−6 cm</quantity>
(vs. crowded leaves); stipules hirsute abaxially with a tuft of fimbriae at the base (vs. glabrous); smaller lamina (9–14 × 7–12 vs. 15–22 × 10–15); longer peduncle (17–25 vs. 
<quantity box="[1041,1158,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="268" unit="cm" value="14.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="11.0">11–18 cm</quantity>
); larger flowers (22–26 × 19–24 vs. 11–12 × 
<quantity box="[351,475,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12 mm</quantity>
); capsule wings unequal (vs. equal) and wings triangular (vs. rounded).
</paragraph>
